it's%20micro-credentials%2C%20not%20degrees%2C%20that%20define%20standout%20hires.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECindy%20Tan%20joined%20Meta%20in%202021%20and%20oversees%20the%20tech%20giant's%20clients%20in%20the%20Asia-Pacific%20region.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BThe%20traditional%20setup%20of%20education%2C%20where%20you%20get%20a%20degree%2C%20is%20table%20stakes%2C%26quot%3B%20Tan%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMeta%20manager%3C%2Fa%3E%20Cindy%20Tan%20says%20earning%20a%20college%20degree%20is%20just%20the%20bare%20minimum%20for%20landing%20a%20tech%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Tan%20says%20it's%20the%20micro-credentials%20you%20earn%20from%20bite-sized%20courses%20that%20will%20impress%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20saying%20that%20we%20should%20all%20not%20do%20our%20degrees%20anymore.%20But%20I%20think%20there's%20more%20to%20it%2C%20whether%20that's%20your%20social%20experiences%20or%20being%20more%20entrepreneurial%2C%26quot%3B%20Tan%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20Business%20Insider%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETan%2C%2047%2C%20joined%20Meta%20in%202021%20and%20is%20a%20managing%20director%20overseeing%20the%20social%20media%20giant's%20clients%20in%20Asia%20Pacific.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Meta%2C%20Tan%20was%20a%20regional%20director%20overseeing%20advertising%20sales%20at%20BBC%20News%20and%20a%20global%20vice%20president%20for%20retail%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftripadvisor-cofounder-ghosted-linkedin-after-leaving-ceo-role-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eat%20TripAdvisor%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20is%20also%20the%20author%20of%20a%20careers%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BOwn%20Your%20MAGIC.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20traditional%20setup%20of%20education%2C%20where%20you%20get%20a%20degree%2C%20is%20table%20stakes%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20real%20opportunity%20is%20in%20micro-programs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETan%20cited%20her%20experience%20taking%20a%20short%20course%20on%20generative%20AI%20through%20a%20Singapore%20government%20initiative%20to%20supplement%20her%20learning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20work%20for%20Meta%2C%20which%20is%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20AI.%20But%20there%20is%20still%20so%20much%20that%20I%20could%20learn%2C%26quot%3B%20Tan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETan%20compared%20learning%20how%20to%20use%20AI%20to%20her%20experience%20of%20picking%20up%20baking%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20look%20at%20YouTube%20videos%2C%20read%20the%20recipes%2C%20but%20you%20are%20not%20going%20to%20learn%20as%20fast%20unless%20you%20actually%20practice%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Tan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20AI%2C%20there%20are%20so%20many%20different%20tools%2C%20so%20many%20different%20applications.%20The%20only%20way%20to%20learn%20is%20to%20try%20to%20practice%20and%20experience%20that%20for%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETan%20said%20people%20looking%20to%20level%20up%20can%20take%20classes%20%E2%80%94%20some%20of%20them%20free%20%E2%80%94%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Flearning%2Fwhat-are-moocs-massive-open-online-courses-faq-edx-coursera%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emassive%20open%20online%20course%3C%2Fa%3E%20providers%20like%20Coursera.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20courses%20will%20help%20candidates%20distinguish%20themselves%20and%20%26quot%3Bset%20them%20up%20for%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20Tan%20said.%20She%20added%20that%20continuing%20to%20pick%20up%20new%20skills%20even%20after%20graduating%20from%20college%20demonstrates%20one's%20curiosity%2C%20inquisitiveness%2C%20and%20passion%20for%20learning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETan%20said%20she%20has%20been%20applying%20AI%20in%20the%20workplace%20and%20at%20home.%20Tan%20said%20even%20her%20daughters%20use%20AI%2C%20whether%20as%20a%20private%20tutor%20or%20to%20create%20comics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20work%2C%20it's%20more%20like%20a%20partner%2C%26quot%3B%20Tan%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20she%20uses%20AI%20to%20summarize%20long%20videos%20or%20to%20conduct%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20the%20personal%20front%2C%20I%20use%20it%20for%20travel.%20Last%20year%2C%20I%20was%20on%20a%20two-week%20trip%20to%20the%20US%2C%20and%20I%20just%20asked%20the%20agent%2C%20'Hey%2C%20give%20me%20a%20two-week%20itinerary%20plan%20from%20the%20east%20coast%20to%20the%20west%20coast%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETan%20isn't%20the%20only%20business%20leader%20who%20values%20job%20seekers%20who%20love%20to%20learn%20new%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccenture%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-question-accenture-ceo-asks-all-staff-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJulie%20Sweet%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20she%20always%20asks%20interviewees%20what%20they%20have%20learned%20recently.%20Sweet%20said%20this%20question%20gives%20her%20a%20quick%20and%20practical%20way%20of%20gauging%20a%20candidate's%20interest%20in%20learning%20new%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20say%2C%20'What%20have%20you%20learned%20in%20the%20last%20six%20months%3F'%26quot%3B%20Sweet%20told%20the%20%26quot%3BIn%20Good%20Company%26quot%3B%20podcast%2C%20in%20an%20episode%20that%20aired%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20someone%20can't%20answer%20that%20question%2C%20and%20by%20the%20way%2C%20we%20don't%20care%20if%20it's%20'I%20learned%20to%20bake%20a%20cake%2C'%20if%20they%20can't%20answer%20that%20question%2C%20then%20we%20know%20that%20they're%20not%20a%20learner%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20working%20in%20Big%20Tech%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20ktan%40businessinsider.com.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.